or an English or something?

01:55.682 --> 01:57.411
You're coming back?

01:58.251 --> 02:01.118
I hope so. Immigration, they make problems.

02:01.421 --> 02:03.355
Maybe Tony can help with that.

02:03.990 --> 02:05.116
Yeah.

02:05.658 --> 02:09.150
What are you doing here?
I thought you were flying out to Naples.

02:09.229 --> 02:11.789
I just dropped off these shirts
from Patsy's guy.

02:11.865 --> 02:14.390
But you should be on your way
to see your old man.

02:14.467 --> 02:16.264
Cancer is everywhere in his body.

02:16.336 --> 02:18.133
Cancer don't respect nothing.

02:18.204 --> 02:21.503
- You know, it started in his guts.
- Do you need any money?

02:22.909 --> 02:24.171
I'm good.

02:24.611 --> 02:26.670
Please call and let us know.

02:28.882 --> 02:30.543
I'm sorry, Tony.

02:30.783 --> 02:33.411
You'll have to get somebody else
to drive you tonight.

02:33.486 --> 02:35.147
Not a problem. Go.

02:38.258 --> 02:40.249
You think he wears a bag?

02:40.827 --> 02:42.055
Who wears what?

02:42.128 --> 02:43.993
You know, a colostomy bag.

02:44.197 --> 02:47.189
- Furio's old man.
- How the fuck would I know that?

02:47.267 --> 02:51.431
Because my ma, maybe, maybe not,
has to get one.

02:51.538 --> 02:53.335
Could we not talk about this?

02:53.406 --> 02:55.772
We could talk about any topic you like, T.

02:55.842 --> 02:56.934
Good.

02:57.810 --> 03:01.109
It's just that now with Ma all squared away
to go to Green Grove...

03:01.181 --> 03:04.639
For fuck's sake, Paulie,
everybody's gonna get old and die.

03:09.889 --> 03:12.653
- Am I driving you tomorrow, too?
- No, I'll drive myself.

03:12.725 --> 03:13.987
I got nothing else to do.

03:14.060 --> 03:16.460
I got a very important meeting, that's all.

03:16.529 --> 03:18.497
It's a delicate situation.

03:23.603 --> 03:25.833
We lucked out with the weather.

03:27.707 --> 03:29.641
So, how's the life of leisure?

03:30.109 --> 03:31.667
Playing golf, ain't I?

03:33.580 --> 03:34.945
Cocksucker.

03:39.919 --> 03:44.185
Seriously, it's good you're pulling back
business-wise like we agreed.

03:44.591 --> 03:46.115
My nephew, I told him.

03:46.192 --> 03:49.628
I'm gonna be speaking through him,
and only through him, as time passes.

03:49.696 --> 03:51.323
- Good.
- Plus Sil.

03:53.099 --> 03:56.000
I don't want to celebrate
my daughter's first kid in prison.

04:02.342 --> 04:05.470
All right, this sit-down in Perth Amboy.
Get a pen and paper.

04:05.545 --> 04:06.739
Hold on.

04:11.618 --> 04:13.745
<i>I can't find a piece of paper.</i>

04:16.022 --> 04:17.011
Shoot.

04:17.089 --> 04:20.753
Tell Paulie to let Patsy run the car operation
while Furio's gone.

04:20.827 --> 04:22.658
<i>Tel Patsy he's got to kick up 10 points.</i>

04:22.729 --> 04:25.425
<i>Seven and a half to me,
two and half to Paulie.</i>

04:25.498 --> 04:26.522
Got it.

04:26.599 --> 04:30.057
You and Sil, you figure out
who pays the Longshore Union how much.

04:30.136 --> 04:32.161
I'll back you up whichever.

04:33.806 --> 04:35.137
What the fuck?

04:36.342 --> 04:38.071
<i>- I'm on it.
- All right.</i>

05:10.076 --> 05:12.567
- A simple yes or no will do.
- Please.

05:15.715 --> 05:18.513
- Artie, hi, how are things?
- Fine.

05:18.651 --> 05:21.051
Did they ever catch those muggers?

05:22.855 --> 05:24.482
Did you leave room for dessert?

05:24.557 --> 05:28.323
We'll have one zabaglione and four spoons.
Coffees, all around.

05:31.397 --> 05:33.991
Bri', can I ask you
a financial-related question?

05:34.067 --> 05:36.331
The last thing the guy wants to do
is talk shop.

05:36.402 --> 05:39.530
Ask him anything you want.
It's all he likes to talk about.

05:39.605 --> 05:40.936
It's no big thing.

05:41.007 --> 05:43.407
Any ideas on what Tony and I should do...

05:43.476 --> 05:46.206
with the proceeds
from the property in Newark we sold?

05:46.279 --> 05:47.746
- A HUD?
- What?

05:48.247 --> 05:51.876
Kid loves Paul Newman movies.
No more grappa for you.

05:52.118 --> 05:53.608
You know what I'm talking about.

05:53.686 --> 05:55.813
Uncle Junior's lot on Frelinghuysen Avenue.

05:55.888 --> 05:58.516
Yeah, that. It all went into the trust.

05:58.791 --> 06:02.522
T- bills, I was able to lock you in
before the rates dropped.

06:03.496 --> 06:06.124
What doesn't this kid know about money?

06:06.232 --> 06:08.462
You know, I trust him 1,000 percent?

06:11.270 --> 06:12.601
Thank you.

06:12.872 --> 06:16.672
- We have so many more of the newborn size.
- I think they're cheaper.

06:17.343 --> 06:19.607
Next year we could put a notice
in the bulletin...

06:19.679 --> 06:23.137
that people whose last names
begin with "A" to "K" bring the newborns...

06:23.216 --> 06:26.481
and "L" to "Z" bring the bigger ones,
or vice versa.

06:26.552 --> 06:30.215
Whatever we give them, the girls
at our ladies' shelter should be grateful.

06:30.289 --> 06:33.452
I mean, nobody told them
to go and have babies without husbands.

06:36.863 --> 06:40.264
I remember his charity toward my family
when Jack died.

06:40.400 --> 06:43.801
I didn't know how to pay the phone bill.
Jackie always did everything.

06:43.870 --> 06:45.735
- There you go.
- Thank you.

06:46.272 --> 06:47.534
I pay bills...

06:48.474 --> 06:51.102
but other than that, it's the same with Tony.

06:51.444 --> 06:53.708
Try to find out where the money is...

06:53.780 --> 06:56.613
how much we have,
and I get such resistance.

06:56.749 --> 07:00.185
I didn't know what we had
until after I buried Jackie.

07:00.853 --> 07:02.150
Was it enough?

07:03.656 --> 07:04.782
Sort of.

07:06.292 --> 07:07.520
Not really.

07:09.028 --> 07:11.121
How much is enough, anyway?

07:11.798 --> 07:13.823
I don't know, that's my point.

07:13.900 --> 07:15.959
Doesn't anything ever change?

07:16.102 --> 07:18.434
Women are supposed to be
partners nowadays.

07:18.504 --> 07:21.803
I'm not a feminist,
I'm not saying 50-50, but Jesus.

07:22.275 --> 07:25.711
<i>You know, I put up with cumare shit.
Pardon my French.</i>

07:26.045 --> 07:28.639
I made my peace with it,
best I could, anyway.

07:28.714 --> 07:31.046
Isn't your cousin Brian
handling your money now?

07:31.117 --> 07:34.553
The big things, the investments.
He's doing well, too.

07:35.188 --> 07:37.554
You know,
I do have to give Tony credit there.

07:37.623 --> 07:39.784
He did meet me halfway with that,
God bless him.

07:39.859 --> 07:41.759
Which was a very big step for him, I know.

07:41.828 --> 07:44.888
- Maybe you have nothing to worry about.
- I don't know.

07:44.964 --> 07:48.092
Tony pulls people into his circle.
I don't know what to think.

07:49.836 --> 07:51.133
Good girl.

07:52.738 --> 07:53.966
Titanium?

07:54.106 --> 07:57.405
The track's freezing up,
it's too hard for aluminum.

07:58.077 --> 08:01.535
Whatever she's got on those feet,
she's a winner.

08:02.782 --> 08:04.374
A little colicky?

08:06.486 --> 08:09.216
You don't feel good, baby girl?
You bad girl.

08:09.288 --> 08:11.620
Fuck this horse-whispering shit.

08:16.596 --> 08:18.359
What is this costing us?

08:19.298 --> 08:20.765
Tony, Valentina.

08:22.468 --> 08:26.427
She works in an art gallery.
Helping me to enlarge my collection.

08:28.474 --> 08:31.671
And this, my chiquita banana, is Pie-O-My.

08:32.044 --> 08:33.272
She's beautiful.

08:33.346 --> 08:36.975
There's no stopping this horse.
She's gonna go all the way to the Breeders'.

08:37.049 --> 08:39.539
We'll do the two geldings next.

08:39.619 --> 08:43.248
Hon, can you come here a sec?
I think I have something in my eye.

08:45.191 --> 08:47.250
Let Dr. Ralphie have a look.

08:50.763 --> 08:53.960
- I don't see anything.
- Maybe you need more light.

08:58.237 --> 08:59.465
What the fuck?

09:00.406 --> 09:03.933
- I can't believe you did this to me.
- It was a joke, hon.

09:04.010 --> 09:05.341
There's nothing funny about it.

09:05.411 --> 09:06.901
There is from where I'm standing.

09:06.979 --> 09:08.742
Besides, it's good luck.

09:09.615 --> 09:12.709
- What?
- It's good luck to step in horseshit.

09:12.952 --> 09:15.250
- Ask any horse person.
- It's true.

09:15.321 --> 09:17.516
Then why aren't you people
walking around...

09:17.590 --> 09:19.854
looking for piles of horseshit
to stomp around in?

09:19.926 --> 09:23.487
- It only works if it's an accident.
- Fucking sick, all of you.

09:23.729 --> 09:25.560
Fucko, where's a hose?

09:33.539 --> 09:37.441
You know, it can be risky trusting him
to have a sense of humor.

09:37.543 --> 09:38.874
Did you think it was funny?

09:38.945 --> 09:42.506
Yeah, but what I think is funny
is what an 8-year-old boy thinks is funny.

09:42.582 --> 09:44.482
Having any fun yourself?

09:44.951 --> 09:46.612
What, you taking a survey?

09:46.686 --> 09:49.553
- Have any interest in art?
- Show the right thing, I do.

09:49.622 --> 09:52.819
There's an artist down in New Hope,
specializes in horses.

09:52.892 --> 09:55.656
Give him a photo of your horse,
he paints a lovely portrait.

09:55.728 --> 09:57.161
It'd look great in your office.

09:57.229 --> 09:59.629
Have a look at my office
before you make that call.

09:59.699 --> 10:00.723
Think about it.

10:00.800 --> 10:03.394
If you're interested, give me a call.

10:06.505 --> 10:09.235
"La Paz. " What's that, Puerto Rican?

10:09.408 --> 10:12.775
<i>Cubana. My mother was Italian,
my father Cuban.</i>

10:12.845 --> 10:14.904
What a dangerous combination.

10:22.054 --> 10:23.681
She gorgeous or what?

10:24.223 --> 10:25.520
Sweet as sugar.

10:29.595 --> 10:32.826
If there's anything you need,
you just press this button.

10:32.898 --> 10:35.662
- Which one?
- This one that I'm showing you.

10:35.968 --> 10:37.265
Safety first.

10:37.336 --> 10:39.463
A friend of yours, Mrs. Cirillo,
might stop by.

10:39.538 --> 10:42.098
She wanted to see you
before you went down for lunch.

10:42.174 --> 10:43.471
Cookie.

10:49.281 --> 10:51.078
Look, just like home.

10:51.283 --> 10:54.184
They're gonna wait on you hand and foot
around here.

10:54.620 --> 10:56.645
Put the boxes in the closet.

10:56.722 --> 10:59.452
And go get the TV. The both of you carry it.

11:01.127 --> 11:02.389
Come on, cowgirl.

11:02.461 --> 11:06.022
Let's go down to the chuck wagon
and see what they're rustling up.

11:07.967 --> 11:11.960
- Paulie, did they bring my bathmat?
- For the fifth time, Ma, yes.

11:13.472 --> 11:15.940
Look who's here to make you feel at home.

11:16.776 --> 11:19.802
- Are you here, too?
- Not yet, but it's all paid for.

11:19.879 --> 11:21.642
I'm gonna move in after my hip surgery.

11:21.714 --> 11:24.911
Minn comes twice a week for lunch,
in the meantime.

11:24.984 --> 11:26.815
She's one of the girls.

11:26.919 --> 11:29.114
Look how you've grown up, Paulie.

11:29.188 --> 11:31.247
I know. I don't understand.

11:31.457 --> 11:34.119
When I was a kid, you two were old ladies.

11:34.193 --> 11:36.889
Now I'm old, and you two are still old.

11:37.697 --> 11:40.291
So, how's Chucky doing, anyway?
Still teaching?

11:40.366 --> 11:43.893
He's been the high-school principal
for the last 10 years or so.

11:43.969 --> 11:45.129
Bergen North.

11:45.204 --> 11:48.401
- He must give you a lot of happiness.
- Except for that wife of his.

11:48.474 --> 11:52.171
- All you ever been was nice to her.
- I know that.

11:52.311 --> 11:56.213
- Come on, girls, I'll take you to lunch.
- I got to use the WC.

11:56.549 --> 11:58.676
She just went 10 minutes ago.

11:59.518 --> 12:02.146
I don't want to embarrass your mother
in the dining room.

12:02.221 --> 12:03.711
So make sure she knows...

12:03.789 --> 12:07.486
she can't sit with me and Minn,
and our other girls.

12:08.294 --> 12:10.785
- What are you talking about?
- We're a set group.

12:10.863 --> 12:13.730
We eat together,
we play Scrabble for money...

12:13.866 --> 12:16.562
and there's really no room at either table.

12:17.002 --> 12:18.629
Come on now, Cook.

12:19.038 --> 12:21.302
I know you girls can work it out.

12:28.581 --> 12:31.948
- Fucking amazing.
- This is how simple it is to change inputs.

12:34.053 --> 12:36.248
Listen to that imaging in stereo mode.

12:36.322 --> 12:38.790
It's like Clapton's sitting right there
at your house.

12:56.442 --> 12:57.636
Great, huh?

12:58.911 --> 13:02.642
We can all watch movies as a family now.
And listen to that.

13:03.649 --> 13:07.176
I think it's great. I'm going food shopping.

13:07.253 --> 13:09.346
<i>Maybe I'll get In the Bedroom.</i>

13:09.421 --> 13:12.413
- What time you want me to wake you up?
- The movie.

13:14.226 --> 13:16.660
Yeah. Good.

13:16.996 --> 13:18.088
Have fun.

13:53.098 --> 13:55.430
<i>- Helo?
- Mr. Wal, please.</i>

13:58.337 --> 14:01.465
<i>- Yeah, can you talk?
- Yeah, I'm on a hotel phone.</i>

14:01.640 --> 14:04.006
<i>So, how are you? What's going on?</i>

14:04.376 --> 14:07.743
<i>I found him, Chuck.
I found the man who kiled Helen.</i>

14:08.280 --> 14:11.113
<i>- What?
- It was me they were after.</i>

14:11.183 --> 14:12.650
<i>Who are they?</i>

14:13.986 --> 14:16.420
<i>Devlin MacGregor and Lentz.</i>

14:17.323 --> 14:20.315
<i>Lentz was supervising
the protocol for RDU-90.</i>

14:20.392 --> 14:24.226
<i>He knew I found out it was causing
liver damage. It was Lentz.</i>

14:26.799 --> 14:28.266
<i>Lentz is dead.</i>

14:28.968 --> 14:30.697
<i>What? How?</i>

14:31.136 --> 14:33.764
<i>He died in a car accident last summer.</i>

14:37.710 --> 14:40.144
<i>Can you prove this about the drug?</i>

14:40.412 --> 14:42.039
<i>Yeah, I think so.</i>

14:43.282 --> 14:45.079
<i>I need your help, Chuck.</i>

14:45.150 --> 14:48.642
<i>Cal Bones at the hospital.
Tel him to give me whatever help I need.</i>

14:48.721 --> 14:50.712
Beautiful looking animal.

14:51.190 --> 14:53.215
Great definition, carriage.

14:55.327 --> 14:58.490
- I'd love to paint her.
- Good.

14:59.932 --> 15:02.093
But what about this deadbeat?

15:02.534 --> 15:04.661
There's no problem cropping you both out.

15:04.737 --> 15:07.638
We could set her in front of the rail
at the track as she is.

15:07.706 --> 15:11.665
Or if you'd prefer something more pastoral,
we can place her in a meadow.

15:11.744 --> 15:15.544
I don't know about that, but can you
leave me in there and just crop him out?

15:15.614 --> 15:19.106
Easy. And frankly, it would be better,
composition-wise.

15:19.752 --> 15:22.220
Go for the pastoral, much more dignified.

15:22.288 --> 15:24.017
And it comes framed?

15:24.123 --> 15:27.615
Exactly as you see that one. $6,500.

15:31.430 --> 15:33.421
All right, you got a deal.

15:36.201 --> 15:38.192
- To Pie-O-Mine.
- My.

15:38.771 --> 15:42.332
- Your what?
- No, the name, it's Pie-O-My.

15:48.247 --> 15:50.681
I'll give you the whole thing now.

15:55.087 --> 15:56.111
There.

15:56.722 --> 15:59.782
I'd better get your receipt.
I'll just be a minute.

16:04.897 --> 16:07.525
<i>Let's not forget
to drink to the beautiful se√±orita...</i>

16:07.599 --> 16:09.863
whose idea this was in the first place.

16:09.935 --> 16:13.666
- I bet you say that to all the girls.
- There's not that many.

16:13.806 --> 16:17.902
And truthfully, the ones that there are,
they don't got many ideas.

16:18.077 --> 16:21.569
We should probably
start heading back soon.

16:21.914 --> 16:23.006
Yeah.

16:24.850 --> 16:27.318
If you want, on the way,
we can stop and eat something.

16:27.386 --> 16:29.013
Yeah, we could definitely stop.

16:34.293 --> 16:35.954
- Like that.
- So good.

16:36.028 --> 16:38.519
- Just like that.
- Yeah, that's so good.

17:05.424 --> 17:06.550
Let me up.

17:38.257 --> 17:40.054
You can see cows from in there.

17:40.125 --> 17:43.026
Sit down and eat before it gets any colder.

17:53.672 --> 17:56.505
- Looks good, doesn't it?
- Mine needed salt.

17:59.378 --> 18:03.041
Jesus fucking Christ,
these fucking hicks can't even get this right.

18:08.487 --> 18:09.886
You did this?

18:10.489 --> 18:12.184
That's very mature.

18:14.293 --> 18:15.317
It's not funny.

18:15.394 --> 18:17.658
I thought you had
an 8-year-old's sense of humor.

18:17.729 --> 18:19.924
Come here and give me a kiss.

18:21.200 --> 18:22.531
I'm eating.

18:26.271 --> 18:28.102
Not anymore, you're not.

18:32.845 --> 18:35.040
What if I promise to be good?

18:36.248 --> 18:37.476
How good?

18:39.451 --> 18:40.543
Good.

18:52.397 --> 18:54.365
Shit, I lost a nail.

19:00.172 --> 19:04.006
We will not be mentioning
anything about any of this to Ralph.

19:06.578 --> 19:09.809
I'll take it.
Can you send it to this person here?

19:10.215 --> 19:12.740
Sure. You want to include a card with this?

19:26.899 --> 19:28.628
Let me have another one.

19:37.943 --> 19:42.039
Round and round she goes,
where she stops, nobody knows.

19:42.114 --> 19:44.309
Place your bets, be a winner.

19:47.853 --> 19:50.515
- I'll take another card.
- Are you sure, dear?

19:54.193 --> 19:57.026
For the love of God, Nucci,
how could you hit on 18?

19:59.965 --> 20:01.728
Give me another one.

20:03.835 --> 20:05.894
That should've been my card!

20:06.505 --> 20:08.166
I could've had 21.

20:08.640 --> 20:10.631
I was hoping for a three.

20:11.543 --> 20:14.478
I'm not sure you understand the fine points.

20:15.080 --> 20:18.140
Maybe you ought to play roulette.
It's right over there.

20:23.222 --> 20:26.658
Round and round she goes,
where she stops, nobody knows.

21:03.528 --> 21:05.519
Goddamn it, Tony!

21:16.675 --> 21:19.200
You did that to me on our honeymoon.

21:19.311 --> 21:22.872
I didn't like it then, and I made you
promise me you'd never do it again.

21:22.948 --> 21:25.576
- It's just a little cold water.
- It's really unpleasant.

21:25.651 --> 21:27.141
Do you remember promising me?

21:27.219 --> 21:30.211
- You can do it back to me.
- I don't want to do it back to you.

21:30.289 --> 21:32.780
- Why not? It's fun.
- Do you remember promising me?

21:32.858 --> 21:34.883
- Yeah, so what?
- So...

21:35.127 --> 21:38.062
This is one promise
I would like you to keep.

21:42.467 --> 21:43.729
Whatever.

22:05.290 --> 22:06.985
This can't be Paulie.

22:07.059 --> 22:08.321
Chucky?

22:08.860 --> 22:11.920
Come here, you
pizza-face-son-of-a-son-of-a-gun you.

22:11.997 --> 22:15.797
Oh, God. Mr. Van Kowenberg,
what did we say about those shoes?

22:16.068 --> 22:19.196
The laces are in my locker,
I was gonna get them after study hall.

22:19.271 --> 22:20.568
Get them now.

22:25.010 --> 22:26.602
Come on, Paulie.

22:30.682 --> 22:33.116
Hard to believe it's been so long.

22:33.919 --> 22:35.511
This is for you.

22:37.622 --> 22:41.388
That's a nice gesture, Paul, but I really can't.

22:41.593 --> 22:44.619
Go on, I got lots of them.
You can't insult me.

22:49.668 --> 22:52.068
- No more glasses?
- I had the Lasik.

22:52.437 --> 22:55.895
- And your face cleared up pretty good, too?
- Cleared up in 10th grade.

22:55.974 --> 22:58.636
See, there you go. Ninth was my last.

23:06.184 --> 23:09.585
So, did your mom tell you
I saw her over at Green Grove?

23:09.654 --> 23:11.918
Apparently, she sees
quite a bit of your mother.

23:11.990 --> 23:15.016
That's just it, Chucky.
They're both residents.

23:15.127 --> 23:17.618
But there seems to be an exclusion.

23:17.829 --> 23:19.387
